  "prompt": "What are all the flavors of Native American Spirit Cigarettes, and what do the colors mean?",
  "response": "Native American Spirit cigarettes, produced by Santa Fe Natural Tobacco Company, are known for their natural and additive-free tobacco. They offer a variety of flavors and blends, each often associated with a specific color on the packaging. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the main flavors and what their colors generally signify:\n\n### **Flavors/Blends:**\n1. **Yellow (Original/Mellow)**\n   - A lighter, mellow blend of natural tobacco.\n\n2. **Blue (Full-Bodied)**\n   - A stronger, full-bodied natural tobacco blend.\n\n3. **Orange (Organic Original/Mellow)**\n   - An organic version of the mellow yellow blend, certified organic tobacco.\n\n4. **Light Blue (Organic Full-Bodied)**\n   - An organic version of the full-bodied blue blend, with a stronger flavor.\n\n5. **Turquoise (American Spirit Blend)**\n   - A balanced blend of full-bodied and mellow tobacco.\n\n6. **Black (Perique Blend)**\n   - Contains Perique tobacco, known for its rich and spicy flavor.\n\n7. **Dark Green (Menthol)**\n   - A full-bodied menthol variety.\n\n8. **Light Green (Organic Menthol)**\n   - An organic version of the menthol blend.\n\n9. **Purple (**\n   - Not a standard flavor, but sometimes associated with unique or limited-edition blends.\n\n10. **Tan/Silver (Filtered Cigars)**\n    - These are technically cigars, not cigarettes, and come in filtered versions.\n\n### **Color Meanings:**\nThe colors on Native American Spirit packaging generally indicate the strength and flavor profile of the tobacco blend:\n- **Lighter Colors (Yellow, Orange, Light Green):** Milder, smoother, or organic variants.\n- **Darker Colors (Blue, Light Blue, Turquoise, Black):** Full-bodied or stronger blends.\n- **Green:** Menthol varieties.\n- **Black:** Unique blends, such as those with Perique tobacco.\n\n### Notes:\n- The brand emphasizes natural and additive-free tobacco, appealing to those seeking a more \u201cpure\u201d smoking experience.\n- Availability of specific flavors may vary by region due to local regulations and market preferences. \n\nAlways check local laws and health advisories regarding tobacco products.",
